        9/21/2010
    








First to Review
        


It was my first time meeting with a Financial Advisor so I didn't know what to expect. But I knew I had to speak to someone regarding my retirement, so I asked my close friend and she referred me to Jimmy at New England Financial. My first impression on him was that he was very friendly and knowledgeable. He gave me some great advice on my IRA and also help me figured out how much money I need and when I could retire all without any obligations. His philosiphy is to educate first so you can make an educated decision. Did not feel pressured at all and made me feel really comfortable.




